bayStackNotificationsMib.name: bayStackNotificationsMib

revisions.description: Version 27: Added bsnAAAUserName, bsnAaaUserAccountNotUsed, bsnAaaAlreadyConnected, bsnAaaIncorrectLogOnThresholdExceeded, bsnAaaMaxNoOfSessionsExceeded, bsnAuditUnsentMessages, bsnAuditRecordEventsFailure, bsnAuditStartUpTrap, bsnAuditShutDownTrap
Version 24: Added bsnUSBInfo and bsnSFPInfo objects.
Version 20: Added bsnUSBInsertion, bsnUSBRemoval, bsnSFPInsertion, bsnSFPRemoval.
Version 19: Added bayStackUnitConfigIndex parameter to bsnSystemUp365Days notification type.
Version 18: Added IP address related parameters to bsnEnteredForcedStackMode notification type.
Version 6: Added bsnLoginFailure and associated objects.

bayStackNotificationsMib.description: Miscellaneous NOTIFICATION definitions for BayStack products.

bsnEapAccessViolationMacAddress.name: bsnEapAccessViolationMacAddress
bsnEapAccessViolationMacAddress.description: The MAC address which caused an EAP access violation.

bsnLoginFailureType.name: bsnLoginFailureType
bsnLoginFailureType.description: The type of login being attempted when the failure occurred.

bsnLoginFailureAddressType.name: bsnLoginFailureAddressType
bsnLoginFailureAddressType.description: The address type contained in the associated value of bnsLoginFailureAddress.

bsnLoginFailureAddress.name: bsnLoginFailureAddress
bsnLoginFailureAddress.description: The IP address from which the login was attempted when the failure occurred.

bsnLoginFailureUsername.name: bsnLoginFailureUsername
bsnLoginFailureUsername.description: The username for which the login failure occurred.

bsnActualStackSize.name: bsnActualStackSize
bsnActualStackSize.description: The actual stack size when a bsnStackConfigurationError notification is generated.

bsnEapUbpFailureIfIndex.name: bsnEapUbpFailureIfIndex
bsnEapUbpFailureIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the port for which UBP policies could not be installed.

bsnEapUbpFailureMacAddress.name: bsnEapUbpFailureMacAddress
bsnEapUbpFailureMacAddress.description: The MAC address for which UBP policies could not be installed.

bsnEapUbpFailureRoleString.name: bsnEapUbpFailureRoleString
bsnEapUbpFailureRoleString.description: The role string of the UBP policies which could not be installed.

bsnTrialLicenseExpirationTime.name: bsnTrialLicenseExpirationTime
bsnTrialLicenseExpirationTime.description: The number of days until a feature trial license will expire. A value of 0 means the license has expired.

bsnTrialLicenseExpirationNumber.name: bsnTrialLicenseExpirationNumber
bsnTrialLicenseExpirationNumber.description: The number of the license that will expire or that has expired.

bsnEnteredForcedStackModeMAC.name: bsnEnteredForcedStackModeMAC
bsnEnteredForcedStackModeMAC.description: The MAC address of a switch which has entered forced stack mode.

bsnEapRAVErrorMacAddress.name: bsnEapRAVErrorMacAddress
bsnEapRAVErrorMacAddress.description: The MAC address that was authorized on a port which could not be moved to the Radius-Assigned VLAN.

bsnEapRAVErrorPort.name: bsnEapRAVErrorPort
bsnEapRAVErrorPort.description: The ifIndex of the port that could not be moved to the Radius-Assigned VLAN.

bsnEnteredForcedStackModeAddressType.name: bsnEnteredForcedStackModeAddressType
bsnEnteredForcedStackModeAddressType.description: The address type contained in the associated value of bsnEnteredForcedStackModeAddress.

bsnEnteredForcedStackModeAddress.name: bsnEnteredForcedStackModeAddress
bsnEnteredForcedStackModeAddress.description: The IP address in use on the switch that entered forced stack mode.

bsnStackProtectionEvent.name: bsnStackProtectionEvent
bsnStackProtectionEvent.description: This object specifies the Stack Protection events which may occur. cannotJoinStack(1) occurs on a BU (base unit) enabled switch which tries to join an existing operational stack. unitIgnored(2) occurs on an operational stack, when a BU enabled switch tries to join the stack.

bsnAaaUserName.name: bsnAaaUserName
bsnAaaUserName.description: The user name of an AAA user account.

bsnConfigurationSavedToNvram.name: bsnConfigurationSavedToNvram
bsnConfigurationSavedToNvram.description: This notification is generated whenever the device saves its configuration to non-volatile storage. The system should limit the frequency with which this notification is generated, as frequent configuration changes could potentially generate too many of these notifications. How the frequency is limitted is an implementation details, but it is suggested that no more than one notification be generated per minute.

bsnEapAccessViolation.name: bsnEapAccessViolation
bsnEapAccessViolation.description: This notification is generated whenever an EAP access violation occurs.

bsnPortSpeedDuplexMismatch.name: bsnPortSpeedDuplexMismatch
bsnPortSpeedDuplexMismatch.description: This notification is generated when a speed or duplex mismatch is detected. Once notification has been sent, further notifications may be sent, but it is suggested these be at least 5 minutes apart.

bsnStackManagerReconfiguration.name: bsnStackManagerReconfiguration
bsnStackManagerReconfiguration.description: This notification is generated by a stackable system when the stack manager detects a problem with a link between stack members.

bsnLacTrunkUnavailable.name: bsnLacTrunkUnavailable
bsnLacTrunkUnavailable.description: This notification is generated when the last trunk is occupied out of a limited number of trunks that can be created. The condition usually occurs because a system has some hardware or software limit on the number of trunks that can be created.

bsnLoginFailure.name: bsnLoginFailure
bsnLoginFailure.description: This notification is generated when an attempt to login to the system fails as a result of an incorrect password.

bsnMLTHealthFailure.name: bsnMLTHealthFailure
bsnMLTHealthFailure.description: This notification is generated when a receiving switch does not receive an expected number of autotopology frames on an MLT in a given time interval from the sending switch(es) on the other end of the MLT. Once notification has been sent, further notifications may be sent, but it is suggested these be at least 5 minutes apart. The ifAdminStatus object reflects the state of the port. The port may be partitioned by the switch or still be active depending on the detection algorithm's control parameters.

bsnTrunkPortDisabledToPreventBroadcastSt.name: bsnTrunkPortDisabledToPreventBroadcastStorm
bsnTrunkPortDisabledToPreventBroadcastSt.description: This notification is generated when an MLT port is disabled as a result of an MLT trunk being disabled.

bsnLacPortDisabledToPreventBroadcastStor.name: bsnLacPortDisabledToPreventBroadcastStorm
bsnLacPortDisabledToPreventBroadcastStor.description: This notification is generated when a LAG port that was port of a trunk is disabled as a result of the LAC setting on the port being turned off.

bsnTrunkPortEnabledToPreventBroadcastSto.name: bsnTrunkPortEnabledToPreventBroadcastStorm
bsnTrunkPortEnabledToPreventBroadcastSto.description: This notification is generated when an MLT port is enabled as a result of an MLT trunk being disabled.

bsnLacPortDisabledDueToLossOfVLACPDU.name: bsnLacPortDisabledDueToLossOfVLACPDU
bsnLacPortDisabledDueToLossOfVLACPDU.description: Generated when a port is disabled due to the loss of a VLACP PDU.

bsnLacPortEnabledDueToReceiptOfVLACPDU.name: bsnLacPortEnabledDueToReceiptOfVLACPDU
bsnLacPortEnabledDueToReceiptOfVLACPDU.description: Generated when a port is enabled due to receipt of a VLACP PDU.

bsnStackConfigurationError.name: bsnStackConfigurationError
bsnStackConfigurationError.description: This notification is generated when the expected size of a stack is not equal to the actual size of the stack.

bsnEapUbpFailure.name: bsnEapUbpFailure
bsnEapUbpFailure.description: This notification is generated when installation of a UBP policy fails following EAP authentication.

bsnTrialLicenseExpiration.name: bsnTrialLicenseExpiration
bsnTrialLicenseExpiration.description: This notification is generated to indicate that a trial license is going to expire soon, or has already expired.

bsnEnteredForcedStackMode.name: bsnEnteredForcedStackMode
bsnEnteredForcedStackMode.description: This notification is generated to indicate that a switch has entered forced stack mode.

bsnTemperatureExceeded.name: bsnTemperatureExceeded
bsnTemperatureExceeded.description: This notification is generated when the temperature of a chassis component has exceeded some threshold. The instance of s5ChasComType included in the notification identifies the component.

bsnEapRAVError.name: bsnEapRAVError
bsnEapRAVError.description: This notification indicates that an Eap client MAC address was authorized on a port, but the port could not be moved to the Radius-Assigned VLAN.

bsnEapRateLimitExceeded.name: bsnEapRateLimitExceeded
bsnEapRateLimitExceeded.description: This notification indicates that incoming traffic on a port exceeded the rate limit settings on that port.

bsnSystemUp365Days.name: bsnSystemUp365Days
bsnSystemUp365Days.description: This notification indicates that the system has been up for 365 days. In stack configuration, bayStackUnitConfigIndex specifies the unit number. For a standalone unit bayStackUnitConfigIndex is always 1.

bsnUSBInsertion.name: bsnUSBInsertion
bsnUSBInsertion.description: This notification is triggered when an USB device is inserted. In stack configuration, s5AgSysUsbTargetUnit specifies the unit number. For standalone, s5AgSysUsbTargetUnit is always 0.

bsnUSBRemoval.name: bsnUSBRemoval
bsnUSBRemoval.description: This notification is triggered when an USB device is removed. In stack configuration, s5AgSysUsbTargetUnit specifies the unit number. For standalone, s5AgSysUsbTargetUnit is always 0.

bsnSFPInsertion.name: bsnSFPInsertion
bsnSFPInsertion.description: This notification is triggered when an SFP module is inserted.

bsnSFPRemoval.name: bsnSFPRemoval
bsnSFPRemoval.description: This notification is triggered when an SFP module is removed.

bsnROPasswordExpired.name: bsnROPasswordExpired
bsnROPasswordExpired.description: This notification is sent when RO password expired.

bsnRWPasswordExpired.name: bsnRWPasswordExpired
bsnRWPasswordExpired.description: This notification is sent when RW password expired.

bsnStackProtection.name: bsnStackProtection
bsnStackProtection.description: This notification is sent when a stack protection event occurs. The event type is specified by the bsnStackProtectionEvent object.

bsnRunScripts.name: bsnRunScripts
bsnRunScripts.description: This notification is sent when a script has been run. It indicates whether the execution was successful or not.

bsnAaaUserAccountNotUsed.name: bsnAaaUserAccountNotUsed
bsnAaaUserAccountNotUsed.description: A bsnAaaUserAccountNotUsed trap signifies that a user account has never been used during a time interval.

bsnAaaAlreadyConnected.name: bsnAaaAlreadyConnected
bsnAaaAlreadyConnected.description: A bsnAaaAlreadyConnected trap signifies that a user is already connected while he attempts to connect again.

bsnAaaIncorrectLogOnThresholdExceeded.name: bsnAaaIncorrectLogOnThresholdExceeded
bsnAaaIncorrectLogOnThresholdExceeded.description: A bsnAaaIncorrectLogOnThresholdExceeded trap signifies that the threshold for incorrect user-entered information is exceeded.

bsnAaaMaxNoOfSessionsExceeded.name: bsnAaaMaxNoOfSessionsExceeded
bsnAaaMaxNoOfSessionsExceeded.description: A bsnAaaMaxNoOfSessionsExceeded trap signifies that the maxim number of current sessions for an AAA user account is exceeded.

bsnAuditUnsentMessages.name: bsnAuditUnsentMessages
bsnAuditUnsentMessages.description: A bsnAuditUnsentMessages trap signifies that the number of audit unsent messages has reached 50% from the total capacity.

bsnAuditRecordEventsFailure.name: bsnAuditRecordEventsFailure
bsnAuditRecordEventsFailure.description: A bsnAuditRecordEventsFailure trap signifies that security log fails to record the events that are required to be recorded.

bsnAuditStartUpTrap.name: bsnAuditStartUpTrap
bsnAuditStartUpTrap.description: A bsnAuditStartUpTrap trap signifies that the audit function starts up.

bsnAuditShutDownTrap.name: bsnAuditShutDownTrap
bsnAuditShutDownTrap.description: A bsnAuditStartUpTrap trap signifies that the audit function shuts down.

bsnAaaUserPasswordExpired.name: bsnAaaUserPasswordExpired
bsnAaaUserPasswordExpired.description: A bsnAaaUserPasswordExpired trap signifies that the password stored for an AAA user account has expired.
